/*  shadertoy-template

Just what you get when you press "new"

This is for DEX3 (Video/Audio mixing software, since it can only use shaders
from shadertoy website via url (as I know so far)
I'm using it to determine the modifications they do to use it
internally. This is just to try to add shaders to DEX manually from hard disk instaedt
E.g. for cases where no internet connection is available.

Maybe useful for other purposes

11/2024 jbond0815

*/

void mainImage( out vec4 fragColor, in vec2 fragCoord )
{
    // Normalized pixel coordinates (from 0 to 1)
    vec2 uv = fragCoord/iResolution.xy;

    // Time varying pixel color
    vec3 col = 0.5 + 0.5*cos(iTime+uv.xyx+vec3(0,2,4));

    // Output to screen
    fragColor = vec4(col,1.0);
}
